# Tor Simulator

This Tor-like onion routing simulator is designed for hands-on learning and rapid experimentation with Torâ€™s core conceptsâ€”without needing a central directory server or real Tor network. Instead of querying a directory authority, each relay self-registers by appending its address and port to a shared nodes_directory.json file, enabling clients to discover peers dynamically. Circuits consist of three hops (Entry â†’ Middle â†’ Exit), each hop performing an ephemeral Diffieâ€‘Hellman handshake over plain HTTP (no TLS), deriving symmetric AESâ€‘128 keys with HKDF, and onionâ€‘encrypting/decrypting payloads in fixedâ€‘size cells.

Logging is colorâ€‘coded per node, so you can visually trace how data moves through the network. Onionâ€‘layer creation (CREATE) and extension (RELAY_EXTEND) are fully simulated, and a simple CLI or GUI drives autoâ€‘build and messageâ€‘fetch flows.


---

## Features

* Builds **3â€‘hop circuits** (Entry â†’ Middle â†’ Exit) using ephemeral Diffieâ€“Hellman key exchanges.
* Onionâ€‘encrypts HTTP requests through multiple hops and decrypts them on return.
* Simple CLI (`main.py`) and optional GUI (`scripts/gui_circuit_builder.py`) interfaces.
* All traffic over **HTTP only**â€”no HTTPS or TLS in the simulated data path.

